lzh_formatted:
  title: 玉河館偶吟
  author: 金訢
  language: lzh
  text: 隙曛斜透弄游塵。靜坐焚香閱此身。盡日掩門來往絶。時時還有賣書人。
korean:
  title: 옥하관 우음
  author: 김흔
  language: kor
  text: |-
    문틈으로 햇빛이 비껴 들어 떠도는 먼지를 희롱하는데
    향을 사르고 고요히 앉아 이 몸을 살펴본다
    한종일 문을 닫고 사람 내왕 끊겼는데
    도리어 때로는 책 파는 사람 있다
  url: https://db.itkc.or.kr/dir/item?itemId=BT#dir/node?dataId=ITKC_BT_1365A_1450_020_0860&viewSync=OT
english:
  title: A Casual Poem at the Jade River Pavilion
  author: Kim Heun
  language: eng
  text: |-
    Through the crack in the door, sunlight slants in,
    playing with dust motes adrift in the air.
    I burn incense and sit in stillness,
    contemplating this fleeting form.

    All day the gate remains shut,
    the world's comings and goings cut off.
    Yet still, from time to time,
    a book merchant passes by.
  footnotes:
    - The 'Jade River Pavilion' likely refers to the poet's retreat or study, a space of solitude and reflection. The juxtaposition of complete isolation with the occasional visitor creates a subtle irony—even in seclusion, commerce and the outside world find their way in.
